<p><strong>Registration</strong></p>
<p>Please <a href="https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/registration?new%20patient=[PATIENT]&amp;adult%20or%20paed=Adult&amp;research%20or%20clinic=Clinic&amp;consult%20or%20sleep=Consult&amp;first%20name=[FIRST_NAME]&amp;last%20name=[LAST_NAME]&amp;dob=[DOB]">click here</a> and complete your registration form before attending for your appointment.</p>
<p><strong>What to bring</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>A Valid Referral &ndash; Indefinite referrals will not be accepted.</li>
<li>Your Medicare/DVA card/Pension card</li>
<li>Any test results (for example, blood tests, X-rays, scans)</li>
<li>A medication list or medications</li>
<li>During the COVID pandemic please ensure that you wear a mask at the clinic. This will help to ensure the safety and wellbeing of yourself and everyone you come in contact with at the clinic.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Screening for COVID 19</strong></p>
<p>Please&nbsp;<strong>do not attend&nbsp;</strong>your appointment if:</p>
<ul>
<li>You have been diagnosed with COVID-19</li>
<li>You have had any of the following symptoms in the last 14 days</li>
<ul>
<li>fever (37.5&deg; or higher)</li>
<li>cough</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>shortness of breath (difficulty breathing)</li>
<li>runny nose</li>
<li>loss of taste</li>
<li>loss of smell.</li>
</ul>
<li>You have developed any other respiratory symptoms</li>
<li>You have been a contact of someone diagnosed with COVID-19</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Payment for your consultation:</strong></p>
<p>The consultation fee for your first visit will be $515.00. If other services are required on the day, additional fees are payable. We accept EFTPOS, credit cards, but no cash or cheques.</p>
<p>We are able to submit your claim to Medicare on site, given we have a valid referral and Medicare details.</p>
<p>Please note that this is a private clinic and Dr Fois doesn&rsquo;t Bulk Bill as a standard rule.</p>
<p><strong>Cancellation Fees</strong></p>
<p>When a patient cancels their appointment or does not attend without giving notice, they prevent another patient from being seen.&nbsp; Therefore, your Doctor requires a 48-hour cancellation notice for any appointment changes.</p>
<p>A charge of $100 will apply for any appointment changes that may occur without appropriate notice.&nbsp;</p>
